{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blog-tsx","path":"/gatsby/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Recently I remade my blog with GatsbyJS. The main reason is that I don't want to create blog by writing html anymore. Gatsby has its "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/part-six/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"support to transformer markdown files into react pages"}]},{"type":"text","value":". During the development with GatsbyJS, I find that GatsbyJS is really a treasure box with its "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/plugins/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"plugins"}]},{"type":"text","value":", its "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/part-eight/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"support for web performance"}]},{"type":"text","value":", its logic of focusing on the web content instead of technical details and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/part-one/#deploying-a-gatsby-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"its focus on the deployment since the beginning of its tutorial"}]},{"type":"text","value":". In this article I will talk a bit with my journey with GatsbyJS."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Evolutions of my portfolio websites from 2015-2019"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"During 5 years, I made 4 versions of my portfolio website. Each new version is pushed by learning of new technology and build tools."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I can remembe